title: Tulsa completes wacky Hail Mary to end first half (Video)
text:
Tulsa completes wacky Hail Mary to end first half (Video) October 23, 2015 0 0 
Tulsa isn’t faring too well against Memphis, but it didn’t stop them from completing a wild Hail Mary touchdown pass at the end of the first half. 
Quarterback Dane Evans avoids a sack and manages to chuck it up to the end zone, where two Tigers defenders collided, allowing Keyarris Garrett to haul it in with one hand. 
Tulsa still went to the half down two touchdowns, but they get points for a pretty cool play. Memphis, meanwhile, may want to sort out their prevent defense in case this comes up in a more important situation. Filed Under:
